# ORIG TITLE    Russia: chemical train explosion injures 17 . 
# ORIG CONTENT  An explosion on a freight train 1,000 kilometres from Moscow has injured 27 people. The accident happened near Belaya Kalitva station in the Rostov-on-Don region. Carrying chemicals and oil products at the time, one of the railcars hit the sixth floor of a residential building. Thirteen people are in hospital and a criminal investigation is looking for safety breaches. 
